---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Pricing Transparency Feline | Healthy Paws Animal Hospital"
  description="Transparent feline pricing for vaccines and lab work at Healthy Paws Animal Hospital in Lake in the Hills, IL."
>
  <!-- Page Header -->
  <section class="bg-hpah-green-light py-16">
    <div class="container text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl mb-4">Pricing Transparency Feline</h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 900px;">
      <p class="mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        Thank you for your interest in Healthy Paws Animal Hospital and the services we provide. As a practice <em><strong>we focus on being personal, professional, and educational</strong></em>. Transparency in what we do and how we do it allows us to provide medical options to clients that are individualized to their pet's and family's needs.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">
        Below we have listed pricing for vaccines and laboratory work commonly discussed during our feline comprehensive wellness exams. Medical care for your pet is never one-size-fits-all. <em><strong>Every pet is unique, and so is every treatment plan</strong></em>. We carefully consider options, benefits, risks, and details, then work with you to create a plan tailored specifically to your pet's needs. At every visit we spend one-on-one time discussing your pet's medical, behavioral, environmental, and social history allowing us to make individualized recommendations.
      </p>

      <p class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Comprehensive Exam – Price $90</p>
      <p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">Our standard exam fee applies to all scheduled wellness and routine sick visits. Same-day emergency sick visits may be priced higher due to the urgent nature of care.</p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl mb-1">Feline Core Vaccinations</h2>
      <p class="text-hpah-text-light italic mb-4">Recommended for all cats</p>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-10">
        <table class="w-full border border-hpah-gray text-sm">
          <thead class="bg-hpah-green-light">
            <tr>
              <th class="text-left p-3 border border-hpah-gray">Vaccine</th>
              <th class="text-left p-3 border border-hpah-gray">Typical Schedule</th>
              <th class="text-left p-3 border border-hpah-gray">Notes</th>
              <th class="text-left p-3 border border-hpah-gray">Price</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="p-3 border border-hpah-gray">Feline Viral Rhinotracheitis (FHV-1), Calicivirus (FCV), and Panleukopenia (FPL)</td>
              <td class="p-3 border border-hpah-gray">Every 3 years (after initial series)</td>
              <td class="p-3 border border-hpah-gray">May require booster depending on prior history</td>
              <td class="p-3 border border-hpah-gray">$31.05</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="p-3 border border-hpah-gray">Rabies</td>
              <td class="p-3 border border-hpah-gray">Every 1-3 years</td>
              <td class="p-3 border border-hpah-gray">Rabies licensure fee is separate</td>
              <td class="p-3 border border-hpah-gray">$57.90 – $120.25</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl mb-1">Feline Non-Core Vaccinations</h2>
      <p class="text-hpah-text-light italic mb-4">Recommended based on lifestyle and risk of exposure</p>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-10">
        <table class="w-full border border-hpah-gray text-sm">
          <thead class="bg-hpah-green-light">
            <tr>
              <th class="text-left p-3 border border-hpah-gray">Vaccine</th>
              <th class="text-left p-3 border border-hpah-gray">Considered For Cats Who…</th>
              <th class="text-left p-3 border border-hpah-gray">Price</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="p-3 border border-hpah-gray">Leukemia (FELV)</td>
              <td class="p-3 border border-hpah-gray">Have exposure to outside</td>
              <td class="p-3 border border-hpah-gray">$56.90</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">
        <strong>Vaccine Supply Fee – $29.00.</strong> A single vaccine supply fee is charged per visit (when vaccines are administered), regardless of the number of vaccines administered during that appointment.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Important Information About Vaccine Scheduling</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
        <li>Vaccine eligibility depends on your pet's previous vaccination history and timing.</li>
        <li>Some vaccines require an initial booster series.</li>
        <li>If a vaccine is overdue, a booster may be required to ensure proper immunity.</li>
        <li>Final recommendations are based on your pet's medical history, risk factors, and current guidelines.</li>
        <li>Your veterinarian will review your pet's records and discuss the appropriate schedule for your individual pet.</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="leading-relaxed">
        <strong>Laboratory Work.</strong> We recommend lab work based on your pet's age, health status, lifestyle, and any current concerns. Testing options vary, with basic screening starting at approximately $160.90.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
